  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6568.64 sitting between max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.77B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (931.9M), dealers are currently in forced buying mode as they hedge short gamma positions below current levels. The massive negative GEX wall at 6500 creates a critical amplification zone where any move lower will trigger aggressive dealer buying to hedge, while a push above 6605 flips dealers to selling mode. The wall break and GEX surge events combined with the sharp negative momentum (-20.3% 1-min, -64.3% 5-min) suggest dealers are scrambling to adjust hedges as key support levels give way.\n\n**Key strikes:** Watch 6500 as the major battleground (massive negative gamma), 6605 as the flip point to dealer selling, and the cluster of negative walls from 6550-6570 that will amplify any directional move.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect volatile swings with dealers buying any dips toward 6500 and selling any rallies above 6605.",
